      • getCoordsInLevel

        Envelope getCoordsInLevel(Point2D center,
                        int level,
                        int w,
                        int h)
                          throws CreateEnvelopeException
        Calculates the bounding box of a zoom level using a center defined in pixels. It's possible to define the center in pixels because a level of resolution has a pixel size.
        Parameters:
        center - center in world coordinates
        level - level of resolution
        w - width in pixels
        h - height in pixels
        Returns:
        Throws:
        CreateEnvelopeException

        tileServer -
